narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You know if you have to take it.
If you like math/want to do advanced math then you have to take it. If you don't have to take it, I'd advise you don't. My enthusiasm for math has taken a dive after this class.
yea, tough tests but good class
Do not take this class unless you have to. If you just need a QR or a calc class there is no point in taking such a terrible course, find something better.

Math 120 is a fairly dry calculus course. Don't expect to be taught many relevant applications of the material. Take it if you are interested in math or want to enter a math-related field, like finance.
I would recommend it because I think the material is valuable. But I would probably recommend ENAS 151 first, as people say it's a better class.
